---
import PageLayout from '../../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import HeroSection from '../../components/HeroSection.astro';
import SignupForm from '../../components/SignupForm.astro';
import { donateUrl } from '../../data/navigation';
---

<PageLayout title="Seniors & Aging with Dignity | Fatmata Barrie" description="Fatmata Barrie's platform on supporting Montgomery County seniors — housing stability, healthcare, transportation, and protecting Social Security and Medicare.">

  <HeroSection title="Seniors & Aging with Dignity" subtitle="Montgomery County's seniors built this community. Fatmata will fight to make sure they can stay, thrive, and age with dignity." />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container priority-layout">

      <div class="priority-body">

        <p class="priority-intro">
          By 2030, adults older than 60 will be more than 25% of Montgomery County's population — and we owe it to them to ensure they are able to age in place, surrounded by community and family. Fatmata understands how the affordability crisis and the weight of property taxes after retirement forces hundreds of county residents out of their homes every year, forcing them to downsize or leave the county. She will be their champion on the County Council.
        </p>

        <div class="priority-section">
          <h2>Bring Down Costs for Older Adults</h2>
          <p>Fatmata will fight to bring down costs for older adults by increasing funding to community healthcare centers, increasing access to community center programs, lowering utility costs, and providing reduced fares for public services — giving seniors the financial breathing room they need to stay in the community they built.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="priority-section">
          <h2>Lower Property Taxes for Retirees</h2>
          <p>Fatmata will fight to lower property taxes for retirees — especially retired county employees, public service employees, and low-income older adults — so residents are able to age in place rather than being pushed out of the homes and neighborhoods where they've spent their lives.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="priority-section">
          <h2>Increase Accessibility and Access to Care</h2>
          <p>Fatmata will work to increase accessibility options and access to care for aging adults so they can find low-cost medical services close to home. No senior should have to choose between their health and their financial security.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="priority-section">
          <h2>Why This Matters for Montgomery County</h2>
          <p>Seniors vote — and they vote in every election because they understand what's at stake. But beyond politics, how a community treats its elders reflects its values. Montgomery County should be a place where the people who built it can afford to stay, can access the care they need, and can age with dignity and respect. Fatmata will make sure it is.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="priority-closing">
          <p>If you or a loved one is a Montgomery County senior navigating housing, healthcare, or transportation challenges — Fatmata wants to hear from you. This fight is personal, and your voice will shape her agenda on the Council.</p>
          <div class="priority-cta-buttons">
            <a href={donateUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-accent">Donate to the Campaign</a>
            <a href="/volunteer" class="btn btn-primary">Get Involved</a>
            <a href="/priorities" class="btn btn-outline">Back to All Priorities</a>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <aside class="priority-sidebar">
        <div class="sidebar-card">
          <h3>Key Actions</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Bring down costs for older adults across healthcare, utilities, and transit</li>
            <li>Lower property taxes for retirees and low-income seniors</li>
            <li>Increase accessibility and access to low-cost medical care</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="sidebar-card sidebar-nav">
          <h3>Other Priorities</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="/priorities/democracy">Defending Democracy</a></li>
            <li><a href="/priorities/education">Education</a></li>
            <li><a href="/priorities/affordability">Affordability &amp; Housing</a></li>
            <li><a href="/priorities/business">Business &amp; Economy</a></li>
            <li><a href="/priorities/womens-health">Women's Health</a></li>
            <li><a href="/priorities/safety">Safer Communities</a></li>
            <li><a href="/priorities/health">Health</a></li>
            <li><a href="/priorities/climate">Climate Justice</a></li>
            <li><a href="/priorities/transportation">Transportation</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </aside>

    </div>
  </section>

  <SignupForm />

</PageLayout>

<style>
  .priority-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 280px;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .priority-intro {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    color: var(--text-light);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--gold);
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  .priority-section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .priority-section h2 {
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    color: var(--primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .priority-section p {
    color: var(--text-light);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .priority-closing {
    background: var(--mint);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    padding: 2rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .priority-closing p {
    color: var(--text-light);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .priority-cta-buttons {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .btn-outline {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.65rem 1.5rem;
    border: 2px solid var(--primary);
    border-radius: 4px;
    color: var(--primary);
    font-family: var(--font-primary);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background 0.2s, color 0.2s;
  }

  .btn-outline:hover {
    background: var(--primary);
    color: #fff;
  }

  .priority-sidebar {
    position: sticky;
    top: 2rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .sidebar-card {
    background: var(--white);
    border: 1px solid var(--light-gray);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
  }

  .sidebar-card h3 {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--teal);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .sidebar-card ul {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: 1.1rem;
  }

  .sidebar-card li {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-light);
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .sidebar-nav li { list-style: none; padding-left: 0; }
  .sidebar-nav ul { padding-left: 0; }
  .sidebar-nav a {
    color: var(--primary);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .sidebar-nav a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .priority-layout { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .priority-sidebar { position: static; }
  }
</style>
